<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>Senate Republicans Introduce Funding Measure to Combat Online Child Abuse</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/19/technology/senate-republicans-funding-combat-online-child-abuse.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/19/technology/senate-republicans-funding-combat-online-child-abuse.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/19/technology/senate-republicans-funding-combat-online-child-abuse.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>As part of the reconciliation bill, the senators have allocated $108 million over three years to add nearly 200 specialists at the Department of Homeland Security.</description><dc:creator>Cecilia Kang</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 14:57:44 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Child Abuse</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Legislation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Children</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Josh Hawley</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/19/multimedia/19biz-CONGRESS-CSAM-cqlk/19biz-CONGRESS-CSAM-cqlk-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Kenny Holston/The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Senator Josh Hawley, Republican of Missouri, has championed the reconciliation bill.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Tired of Hacked Passwords? Help Is on the Way.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/13/technology/personaltech/passwords-managers-passkeys.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/13/technology/personaltech/passwords-managers-passkeys.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/13/technology/personaltech/passwords-managers-passkeys.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Apps from Apple, Google and others can assist in making your online accounts more secure, even as new ways of logging in continue to take off.</description><dc:creator>J. D. Biersdorfer</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 09:02:26 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Smartphone</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Apple</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Samsung</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">None</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Android</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mobile Apps</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Service Content</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/13/technology/personaltech/13BIZ-TECHTIP-TOP/13BIZ-TECHTIP-TOP-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>1Password</media:credit><media:description>A password manager, like the 1Password app shown here, serves as a secure vault for all your user names, passwords and other private information.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Peter G. Neumann, Who Warned of Computer Security Risks, Dies at 93</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/17/technology/peter-g-neumann-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/17/technology/peter-g-neumann-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/17/technology/peter-g-neumann-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>For decades, he criticized the industry’s lax attitudes toward computer security and individual digital privacy. He also developed solutions.</description><dc:creator>John Markoff</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 21:27:18 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Peter G Neumann</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">DARPA</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SRI International</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Obituary</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/17/multimedia/00neumann-kjbp/00neumann-kjbp-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Jim Wilson/The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Peter G. Neumann in 2012. At his death, he was still working full time on advanced computer security design being adopted by companies like Google and Microsoft. </media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Meta Reassigns 7,000 Employees to Focus on A.I.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/18/technology/meta-reassigns-7000-employees-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/18/technology/meta-reassigns-7000-employees-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/18/technology/meta-reassigns-7000-employees-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The company announced the changes two days before it plans to lay off 10 percent of its work force, or about 8,000 employees.</description><dc:creator>Eli Tan</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 21:47:54 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Layoffs</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Furloughs</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Meta</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mark E Zuckerberg</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/18/multimedia/18biz-meta-ai-1-jvzc/18biz-meta-ai-1-jvzc-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Adrienne Grunwald for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>The new Meta Lab flagship store, which sells tech like smart glasses and virtual reality headsets, on Fifth Avenue in Manhattan. </media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Elon Musk Loses $150 Billion Suit Against OpenAI and Sam Altman</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/18/technology/elon-musk-lawsuit-openai-sam-altman.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/18/technology/elon-musk-lawsuit-openai-sam-altman.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/18/technology/elon-musk-lawsuit-openai-sam-altman.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A nine-member jury found that Mr. Musk had waited too long to sue. The setback for the tech mogul frees OpenAI to continue in the artificial intelligence race.</description><dc:creator>Cade Metz and Mike Isaac</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 21:31:32 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Decisions and Verdicts</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Sam Altman</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Greg Brockman</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Yvonne Gonzalez Rogers</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Oakland CA</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Nonprofit</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/18/multimedia/18biz-ai-trial-ledeall-brockamn-glbh/18biz-ai-trial-ledeall-brockamn-glbh-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Jason Henry for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>OpenAI’s president, Greg Brockman, right, was also named in Mr. Musk’s lawsuit. </media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Struggling With Phone Addiction? Try These Remedies.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/30/technology/personaltech/phone-addiction-remedies.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/30/technology/personaltech/phone-addiction-remedies.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/30/technology/personaltech/phone-addiction-remedies.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Counting minutes is a poor way to curb phone habits. Real antidotes, experts say, include mindful parenting, curated content and human connection.</description><dc:creator>Brian X. Chen</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 09:01:48 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Screen Time (Device)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Addiction</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mobile Apps</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Children</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/names